Class FIODataPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • main.FIODataPoint

  • public class FIODataPoint
extends java.lang.Object
    Representation of a Data point.

    Helper used for handling Data points objects. More information available here.
    Version:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    David Ervideira, Theo FIDRY (theo.fidry@gmail.com)

      • getMoonPhase

        public final double getMoonPhase()
                          throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get a number representing the fractional part of the lunation number of the given day. This can be thought of as the “percentage complete” of the current lunar month: a value of 0 represents a new moon, a value of 0.25 represents a first quarter moon, a value of 0.5 represents a full moon, and a value of 0.75 represents a last quarter moon.

        If no such slot has been found, an exception is thrown.
        Returns:
        [0; 1]
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getNearestStormDistance

        public final int getNearestStormDistance()
                                  throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get numerical value representing the distance to the nearest storm. (This value is very approximate and should not be used in scenarios requiring accurate results. In particular, a storm distance of zero doesn’t necessarily refer to a storm at the requested location, but rather a storm in the vicinity of that location.)

        If no such slot has been found, an exception is thrown.
        Returns:
        storm distance
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getNearestStormBearing

        public final long getNearestStormBearing()
                                  throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get a numerical value representing the direction of the nearest storm in degrees, with true north at 0° and progressing clockwise. (If nearestStormDistance is zero, then this value will not be defined. The caveats that apply to nearestStormDistance also apply to this value.)

        If no such slot has been found, an exception is thrown.
        Returns:
        storm direction
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getPrecipitationIntensity

        public final double getPrecipitationIntensity()
                                       throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get a numerical value representing the average expected intensity of precipitation occurring at the given time conditional on probability (that is, assuming any precipitation occurs at all). A very rough guide is that a value of 0 in./hr. corresponds to no precipitation, 0.002 in./hr. corresponds to very light precipitation, 0.017 in./hr. corresponds to light precipitation, 0.1 in./hr. corresponds to moderate precipitation, and 0.4 in./hr. corresponds to heavy precipitation.

        If no such slot has been found, an exception is thrown.
        Returns:
        intensity of precipitation
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getPrecipitationIntensityMax

        Get the numerical value representing the maximum expected intensity of precipitation on the given day in inches of liquid water per hour.

        If no such slot has been found, an exception is thrown.
        Returns:
        intensity of precipitation
        Throws:

      • getPrecipitationType

        public final java.lang.String getPrecipitationType()
                                            throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get the type of precipitation occurring at the given time. If defined, this property will have one of the following values: rain, snow, sleet (which applies to each of freezing rain, ice pellets, and “wintery mix”), or hail. (If precipIntensity is zero, then this property will not be defined.)

        If no such slot has been found, an exception is thrown.
        Returns:
        type of precipitation
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getCloudCover

        public final double getCloudCover()
                           throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get a numerical value between 0 and 1 (inclusive) representing the percentage of sky occluded by clouds. A value of 0 corresponds to clear sky, 0.4 to scattered clouds, 0.75 to broken cloud cover, and 1 to completely overcast skies.

        If no such slot has been found, an exception is thrown.
        Returns:
        [0; 1]
        Throws:

      • isValid

        public static boolean isValid(net.sf.json.JSONObject data)
        Check if the JSON given has the required information for being processed as an alert.

        Data entries checked:
        • title: short text summary of this alert
        • expires: UNIX time at which this alert will cease to be valid
        • description: detailed text description of this alert (optional)
        • URI: HTTP(S) URI that contains detailed information about this alert
        Non optional data are required or the JSON is considered as invalid.
        Check if the entries are convertible to strings.
        Parameters:
        data - JSON checked | null
        Returns:
        true on success, false otherwise

      • update

        public boolean update(net.sf.json.JSONObject data)
        Updates this instance with the given JSON.

        The JSON must be valid or this instance will be emptied.
        Unrecognized values are disregarded and not stored.
        Parameters:
        data - data JSON source | null
        Returns:
        true on success, false otherwise

        public boolean isEmpty()

      • equals

        public boolean equals(FIODataPoint dataPoint)
        Compares this instance to another data point to determine if they are equals.

        Two dataPoints are considered as equals if they contains the same informations. String are case sensitive and an empty string is not equal to a space. The order of the data does not matter.
        Parameters:
        alert - alert to which compare this instance | null
        Returns:
        true if equal, false otherwise
